          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Completing their Programs",
          "Completed (0) vs Abandoned (1)",
          "7108 students",
          "All courses in an Australian University",
          "Admission Data, Academic History, Course Descriptions",
          "[Basics For Admission Description, Has Previous Tertiary Studies, Higherst Schoool Qualification Description, Current Full Time Status, Current Student Mode Numeric, Current Prior Activity Description, Age Description, Gender, Grade MArk Mean, Grade Mark Max, Grade Mark Deviation From Class Mean, Papers Failed for Student Academic Year, Online Learning Has Passed Assessment Count Z-Score, Total Qualification Percent Completed, Online Learning Submitted Assignments Z-Score, Papers Withdrawn For Student Academic Year, Online LEarning Pages Viewed Count Z-Score, Online Learning Quiz Taken Count Zcore, Online Learning Forum Post Created Count Zscore, Online Learning On Time Submission Count Zscore, Programme Title Programme Credits Required]",
          "End of Program",
          "Students were represented per year. In essence, this means that the same student who completed a 3-year program would feature 3 times in the dataset, always with the flag completed.\n\nFeatures can be summarized by 4 overarching categories:\n\nAcademic performance , learning behavbiors, immuatable learner characteristics, Program Characteristics.\n\nInstead of working with absolute counts, authors opted to relativize their variables among their co-hort. Data was standardized. \n\nMissing Values were filled using 0. Categorical Variables were subjected to Binary Encoding.\n",
          "CatBoost, Random Forest, SVM, Logistic Regression, DT, GBoost, kNN, Naive Bayes, Random Guessing, ZeroR",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{F1-Score: 0.945 - CatBoost, Accuracy: 0.92 - CatBoost, AUC: 0.883 - CatBoost, Recall: 1 - ZeroR, Precision: 0.925 - CatBoost}",
          "Peescriptive Modelling part shows only hypothetical scenarios. Predictive modelling follows a formative and a summative perspective.\n\nDuring th formative perspective, the models evaluate outcomes for specific thresholds of course completion. On the Summative Perspective, the authors attempt to predict end-of-program completion.\n\nHyper-Parameter Tuning for Candidate Models was executed via a Random Search. Feature interepretability was done using SHAP.\n\nThis work is positive in the sense that it provides a picture into what can be done after predicting learner success.",
          "Lacks deployment of Prescrictive Model Part.\n\nOnly results from the summative approach - predicting at the end of the program - are shown.\n\nImbalance between classes is not addressed meaningfully.\n\nFeature set considered is limited to Actionable Features, which hinders the rpedictive performance of the models. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
